# Patch 0003 — Per-workspace search engine (Kavacha Workspace Identities, Phase 2).
#
# What: adds an optional `searchProvider` field (engine name) to Zen's space
# object. Switching to a space with an override makes that engine the default
# search engine; spaces without one restore the profile's baseline (remembered
# in the kavacha.workspaces.baseline-search-engine pref, cleared on restore).
# A "Set Search Engine" submenu in the space actions menu sets/clears it, and
# manually changing the default engine while an override is active adopts the
# new engine into the workspace instead of reverting on the next switch.
# Engines synced from another device but not installed here are ignored.
# Why a patch: the switch chokepoint (#performWorkspaceChange) and the space
# actions menu live in Zen's source; the field itself persists + syncs for
# free through Zen's session store and spaces sync engine.
# Touches: src/zen/spaces/ZenSpaceManager.mjs,
#          src/browser/base/content/zen-panels/popups.inc,
#          locales/en-US/browser/browser/zen-workspaces.ftl.
# Independent of 0001/0002 content-wise; apply in order regardless.
